        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 1:44PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 144 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 25
miles east of Castle Valley, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation and
outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Mesa
County.

This includes Colorado 141 between mile markers 98 and 105.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
